Peaks

This page displays a list of peaks detected by LifeTracer.

  • The csv_file_name column indicates the file to which the peak belongs.
  • The peak_area column refers to the total intensity of a peak, calculated as the sum of intensities within each rectangular region (peak).
  • RT1_start, RT2_start, RT1_end, and RT2_end indicate the start and end points of the rectangular region (peak). RT1_center and RT2_center represent the center point of the rectangle.
  • m/z refers to the mass-to-charge ratio.
